you can see in the page source that the links are not proper:
```&lt;meta name="author" content="Miguel Raz Guzmán Macedo"&gt;
  &lt;title&gt;DoctorDocstrings.jl&lt;/title&gt;

  &lt;link rel="icon" type="image/png"  href="/assets/favicon.ico"&gt;

  &lt;!-- CSS --&gt;

   &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="/libs/highlight/styles/atom-one-dark.css"&gt;

  &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/bootstrap.min.css"&gt;```
the paths should be `DoctorDocstrings.jl/css/...` this is set by the prepath in config.md (which you've set properly) and activated when you run the `optimize` . I don't have time to look into this right now but that's why you're seeing something ugly, basically the address of the CSS file is incorrect
